  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Persistent atrial fibrillation (AF) is a common and distressing condition, that can cause
      significant symptoms. AF ablation is a recognised technique to treat persistent AF, but can
      be technically difficult. This study compares percutaneous ablation to thoracoscopic surgical
      AF ablation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
